node.text:
We’ve made purchase agreements for 2️⃣7️⃣0️⃣ new aircraft – the largest order in our history and biggest by a single airline in a decade.⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
Meet our signature interior, your new onboard experience which will be on board our new planes from @boeing and @airbus as well as retrofitted on all other narrow-body planes planned by 2025. ⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
🧳 Larger overhead bins to fit one carry-on for every passenger⁣⁣
📺 Seatback entertainment and power outlets at every seat⁣⁣
🎧 Bluetooth connectivity throughout the cabin meaning your headphones connect directly to entertainment ⁣⁣
💻 Industry’s fastest available inflight WiFi⁣⁣
💺 More Economy Plus and United First seats than before ⁣⁣
 ⁣⁣
Tap the link in our bio to learn more. 🎉

node.text:
It's electric! ⚡️
 
We signed an agreement with @heartaerospace to acquire the ES-19 aircraft, a 19-seat electric airliner that has the potential to decarbonize regional air travel. United Express regional partner @mesa_airlines has also agreed to purchase and operate the ES-19. 

The ES-19 can fly up to 250 miles with minimum noise and zero operational emissions and are set to take flight in 2026. Examples of potential routes include Chicago O’Hare (ORD) to Purdue University Airport (LAF) and San Francisco (SFO) to Modesto City-County Airport (MOD). 

United Airlines Ventures and Breakthrough Energy Ventures are both identifying and building companies that can help the planet reach net-zero greenhouse gas emissions which will help us build a carbon-neutral airline and reach our net-zero greenhouse gas emissions goal.
